The new Kilifi Creek jetty will be launched soon to transport tonnes of ballast and other construction material worth billions of shillings from Kilifi county to Lamu for the Lapsset project.The jetty is being constructed by a Chinese company. Mining materials will be transported from the Jaribuni quarry in Kilifi county.On Tuesday, Mining CS Dan Kazungu inspected the jetty, whose construction is at an advanced stage.Speaking to the Star on the phone yesterday, he said hundreds of jobs will be created.&ldquo;The project will create wealth for investors, the national and county governments as well as communities,&rsquo;&rsquo; Kazungu said.He said the mining sector is expected to experience exponential growth next year.